           =20
                <div class=3D"question-container">
   =20
        <p>A fast food restaurant gets an average of 2.8 customers approach=
ing the register every minute.</p>

<p>Assuming the number of customers approaching the register per minute fol=
lows a <a href=3D"https://brilliant.org/wiki/poisson-distribution/" class=
=3D"wiki_link" title=3D"Poisson distribution" target=3D"_blank">Poisson dis=
tribution</a>, what is the probability that 4 customers approach the regist=
er in the next minute? </p>

<p>Round your answer to 3 decimal places.</p>

   =20
</div>
           =20

            <div class=3D"solution-container hide">
                <br><br>
                The correct answer is: <strong>0.156</strong>
               =20
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<p></p>

<p>The Poisson distribution can be used to calculate the probabilities of "=
less than" and "more than" using the <a href=3D"https://brilliant.org/wiki/=
probability-rule-of-sum/" class=3D"wiki_link" title=3D"rule of sum" target=
=3D"_blank">rule of sum</a> and <a href=3D"https://brilliant.org/wiki/proba=
bility-by-complement/" class=3D"wiki_link" title=3D"complement probabilitie=
s" target=3D"_blank">complement probabilities</a>.</p>

